# .actrc — defaults for `act` local workflow testing.
#
# Usage:
#   act -j actionlint          # run a single self-test job
#   act -j yamllint            # run yamllint only
#   act -j shellcheck          # run shellcheck only
#   act pull_request           # simulate a PR event
#   act -l                     # list available jobs
#   act push --secret-file .act.env  # with secrets
#
# Caveats (per SPEC.md §18.2):
#   - act CANNOT simulate: reusable workflow calls (workflow_call),
#     repository_dispatch, environment secrets, concurrency groups,
#     permissions model, or step-security/harden-runner egress auditing.
#   - act CAN simulate: single-job linting (actionlint, yamllint, shellcheck),
#     simple shell logic, checkout + script execution.
#   - For full integration testing, use the e2e test repository.
#
# Recommended local workflow:
#   1. Run `act -j actionlint` to validate workflow syntax
#   2. Run `act -j yamllint` to validate YAML style
#   3. Run `act -j shellcheck` to lint shell scripts
#   4. For zizmor/verify-sha/bats, run tools directly:
#      zizmor --format plain .
#      bash .github/scripts/verify-sha-consistency.sh
#      bats tests/ --recursive
#
--container-architecture linux/amd64
--detect-event
-P ubuntu-latest=catthehacker/ubuntu:act-latest
--env-file .act.env
